{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HLMHwVNUSvuJU7XoseK8LK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem:** The `es-secure-settings` secret didn't exist, there was no MinIO service, the `repository-s3` plugin wasn't installed on any node, and the `es-backups` bucket didn't exist.\n\n**Solution:**\n1. **Created MinIO service** — `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000` (the deployment existed but had no service)\n2. **Created `es-secure-settings` secret** — stores `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (both `minioadmin`) as Kubernetes Secret data, not in elasticsearch.yml or env vars\n3. **Patched both StatefulSets** (`es-cluster` and `es-data`) with an init container that:\n   - Installs the `repository-s3` plugin and copies it to a shared `emptyDir` volume\n   - Reads credentials from the secret and populates the Elasticsearch keystore, copying it to another shared `emptyDir` volume\n   - The main container mounts these volumes so the plugin and keystore persist across container restarts (but not pod replacements — the init container re-runs on each pod start, which is correct)\n4. **Created `es-backups` bucket** in MinIO via `mc` directly\n5. **Registered `minio-repo`** as an S3 repository with `path_style_access: true` and `protocol: http`\n6. **Created `snapshot-1`** — state `SUCCESS`, 3/3 shards across all 5 nodes"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":501,"cache_read_input_tokens":58531,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":501},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5df30696-b7bd-4a6a-9f40-54c553963ab0","uuid":"9596f0b9-0c5c-4f9b-b329-38971b0cffbc","request_id"